            <p class="sans-serif-body-2 text-dirty-grey py-4 fade-in">Golden Bear Studios is named after Lucy, my Mini Goldendoodle, who, like all good dogs, has been my light and grounding force (all whilst looking consistently adorable).</p>
            <p class="sans-serif-body-2 text-dirty-grey py-4 fade-in">I studied Fine Art at university before diving headfirst into the world of digital design. I started out in hybrid roles that combined web development and design - learning to write clean code alongside crafting interfaces - which gave me a solid foundation in both the technical and visual sides of digital work.</p>
            <p class="sans-serif-body-2 text-dirty-grey py-4 fade-in">Over the years, I’ve led design teams, shaped digital products, and collaborated with brands at scale - experiences that sharpened my craft and taught me the power of thoughtful, strategic design.</p>
            <p class="sans-serif-body-2 text-dirty-grey py-4 fade-in">But somewhere along the way, I felt the pull to reconnect with what first drew me to design in the first place: the joy of making, the importance of balance, and the value of work that feels personal. Golden Bear Studios is my space to do just that - to bring creativity and clarity to projects that matter, blending an artist’s eye with a designer’s mindset, and backed by technical know-how.</p>
            <p class="sans-serif-body-2 text-dirty-grey py-4 fade-in">Whether I’m working with a global brand or an independent founder, I care most about doing good work with kind people - and keeping the spirit of Golden Bear Studios in every project.</p>

